## Characters:

### Ship
- Hector -> captain
  - Greedy / Wants a better furture for him and Fay
  - Wants to do good, but usually does bad, excuse his action by blaming it on the harsh world around him
  - Is a man who wants to do good but does evil knowingly, worse or better than a man who does evil beliving it to be good.
- Fay -> Hectors apprentice
  - Does everything to appease Hector
  - Strong willed but with a closed heart
  - helps children around her as she sees others as potentially evil
  - Crush on Rob Dolson
  - Don't like physical contact (abused as a child)
  - Wants to be seen as tough and heartless as it is safer that way
- Mr. Farrow -> Second in command
  - Wise older man
  - Surgeon and map reader
  - Has taken Rob Dolson under his wing
  - Not as tough as Hector
  - The most loyal pirate there is
- Mr. Torp -> old seadog, ready to do Hectors bidding
  - Tough killer
  - Not as soft hearted as Hector
  - Man of few words
  - Takes the crews rules very seriously
- Mr. Bern -> sailor under Hector though a bit too violent even for Hector
  - Cruel pyromaniac
  - Loves to hurt others
  - Is greedy but likes to take coin by violence even more
  - Likes younger girls
  - Mr. Dolson -> young sailor on hectors ship
    - romamce between him and Fay
    - Mr. Farrow takes care of the lad
    - Coward
    - Wants to be respected
    - Young
    - Fay teaches him, sees him a bit as a wounded bird
    - Wants to be loyal, but fear and ambition
  - Frederic -> name of the monk secretary
    - Secretly kings son
    - bold and brave, bred to lead men
    - Watched over by the preacher
  - Preacher
    - Worked as court priest
    - Came from a poor family (stable boy)
    - Used to be a war priest
    - Shrewd
    - Wants to be a fanatical beliver, wants to reach his goal even if he has to be somewhat pratical, is uncrompoising regarding his true goal.
  - Mr. Halton -> new boatswain for Mr. Bern
  - Mr. lansly -> new gunner for mr. Bern
  - Mr. Barlow -> bern lackey


- Barish -> guard at le Baiser
- Madame PÃ©ronne -> owner of le Baiser
- brenda -> owner of the wallow wrench
- Eiras -> former abbot of the monestratry of renetra
- Marrick company -> oil trading company
- cap'n Tarren -> Hectors old captain
- Marie -> little girl working at Le Baiser

## Things:
- book of Brajit -> knowledge about the isle of saint moru
- catchers light -> a glowing stone used by the monks at La Trion to catch children
- Wolfay -> pain remedy and sleep inducing flower

## Ships:
